subSection.paragraph:
Morphology and reproduction. As far as size and overall morphology are concerned, the three species of the
O . diadema
group are typical members of
Ophryotrocha
. Their coherence as a group has been demonstrated by phylogenetic analyses employing electrophoresis (
Pleijel & Eide 1996
) and DNA sequences (Dahlgren el al. 2001 ;
Heggøy et al. 2007
). The clade can further be characterised by the combination of a number of morphological and reproductive attributes which are discussed below. Most of these are also found in other members of the genus; however, it is the combination of these features that characterise the three species as a coherent group.

(
3
) Dorsal and ventral parapodial cirri are absent.
